State files an Amended Information charging 1 ct. PTC Theft, contrary to Section 943.20(1)(a) & 939.05 and 2 cts. Felony Tax Fraud, contrary to Section 71.83(2)(b)1 of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.   Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 1 for further proceedings.   Waiver of Right to Preliminary Hearing.   
Count 2 - Fraud-rendering income tax return - Guilty plea.   
Count 3 - Fraud-rendering income tax return - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 1 PTC Theft.   Motion granted.   
Sentences are withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for thirty-six (36) months.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) Provide DNA sample;
3) Maintain full-time employment or work search;
4) Pay resittution to Federal Mogul in the amount of $400.00 joint and several with Jonathan W. Thompson;
5) Defendant is not allowed to be involved in the salvage business or profit from any salvage business as a shareholder or officer;
6) Perform 200 hours of community service work;
7) On Count 2 - Twelve (12) months jail, under the Huber Law.  Six (6) months, to be served up front commencing immediately.  Six (6) months, stayed to be imposed at the agent's discretion.  Court authorizes out of county travel for employment purposes.  
8) Pay tax penalties as being negotiated. 
9) Pay costs of action; 
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights. 
Notice of Right to SeekPostconviction Relief.  
Voter Ineligibility Notice and Acknowledgment.  
Minutes.
